## Anti-Patterns (What NOT to Do)

### ❌ Do NOT Make Strategic Decisions

**Wrong:** "This strategic analysis is too complex. I'll escalate to PRIME."
**Right:** "Spawn instruction received for Gemini 2.5 Pro. Executing as requested."

### ❌ Do NOT Decompose Tasks

**Wrong:** "PRIME said 'analyze architecture'. I'll break it into 5 sub-tasks."
**Right:** "PRIME provided 10 discrete tasks. Spawning 10 agents as instructed."

### ❌ Do NOT Skip PRIMARY Method

**Wrong:** Always using fallback: `qwen --openai-base-url http://localhost:47821/v1 -m google/gemini-2.5-pro --yolo -p "..."`
**Right:** Try PRIMARY first: `gemini --yolo -p "..."`, then fallback to qwen CLI if needed

**Rationale**: Native `gemini` CLI is faster, more reliable, and officially supported by Google

### ❌ Do NOT Exceed Capacity Limits

**Wrong:** Spawning 15 Gemini agents via single orchestrator (exceeds 10 limit)
**Right:** Spawning up to 10 Gemini agents, or using multiple orchestrators for larger workloads

### ❌ Do NOT Omit RFC 2119 Compliance

**Wrong:** Spawning agents without RFC 2119 compliance instructions
**Right:** Including RFC 2119 compliance requirements in every spawned agent's prompt

### ❌ Do NOT Spawn Leaders

**Wrong:** Spawning gemini-swarm-leader instances (3-tier - deprecated)
**Right:** Spawning gemini-agent instances (Gemini 2.5 Pro) that report to PRIME (2-tier)

